Wednesday May 6th. .

----Early this morning there was a power outage and it seems to have affected our system. We are working to get it fixed. We've asked businesses around us, and they seem to be ok. So we are not sure why our system isn't back and up and running.
¬∞ At this time, I made the decision to have us close for the day. Give our cook the full day off , Kevin has been amazing and has been cooking your food since this has all started. All three of us want to thank you for your continuous support and we will be back and running tomorrow to serve you! üå¥
We apologize for the inconvenience .

Thank you,
Kayla, Jess & Kevin ‚ù§Ô∏è

post_text:
This is a hard season for small businesses. We have lost so much during this, but we also have gained SO much! The outpouring love and support we have gotten from our customers & family is something you can't put into words. So I will say one thing "God is good. All the time" even in this season, he is reminding me daily that we got this. We will be stronger because of this. Our relationships with people has grown more ( if that's even possible) and we aren't going anywhere. We are here to stay and serve our valley for as long as we can. @palmscafe2010 - Thank you Rogue Valley for supporting us! üå¥#8yearsstrong #supportlocal
We also encourage supporting other small businesses. Central point offers tons of options for your cravings !

post_text:
√∞¬ü¬é¬∂ "People let me tell you about my best friend"√∞¬ü¬é¬∂
This girl lights up a room when she walks in! Filling your heart with joy and laughter, she is nothing less of an angel to be around. You ask her what her secret is , she will always tell you God!! I've never been much of a "believer " in the sense of religion , but I will tell you she has changed that for me in some way or another. I've watched her walk through everyday struggles with grace and ease. Always choosing Faith first. Inspite of how she was truly feeling inside. Let me tell you she has been through the darkness, always choosing the light. Always saying things like " everything will be ok, God always provides " " I just have to stay strong, I know I'll get through this. I know God is working in my life" again not being a religious person this never put a poor taste in my mouth, for she never shoved it down my throat. I was always attracted to the Words and faith that she spoke, and lived by. Her heart strings are calling her to Serbia this March, for a mission trip to serve God, by serving others. She will be hosting an event or two to help raise money for her trip. (Details to follow) There is also a Jar at the restaurant for those who know and love her. If you can and would like to help support her , I know she is very appreciative of anything. Thank you, and we love our Palms Family!!! I love you Kayla Marie Adams

post_text:
This is George He is a 95 year old WWII Veteran.
He is one of our regulars, he's been coming in for years. Every time he comes in, someone pays for his meal . He always replies with
" I was just doing what I was suppose to "
And tears of gratitude start to well up .
Someone bought a gift certificate to keep tabs on Geroge, so that he didn't have to pay for his meals for a while. Customers continue to put money on George's tab. It's been over a year since George has had to buy a breakfast thanks to the generosity of our customers who continue to add to his tab.
Thank you all for keeping this chain of love going for this wonderful man, and very deserving Veteran. And a very special thank you to those who sit and talk with him. He is beyond GREATFUL and leaves in tears every time.
From the bottom of our hearts Geroge THANK YOU, THANK YOU , THANK YOU!!!!!
THANK YOY FOR YOUR SERVICE.
WE SALUTE YOU!!!

post_text: Good morning! As some of you know, I have been going to nursing school this last year. With the intensity of the program, trying to run the restaurant, and raise my children, my sanity started to slide. I brought in a partner last August and it's bittersweet but I have decided to step down! I am grateful for the relationships I have formed, the support I have been given, and for the growth we have seen over the last four years. Jess, Joe, and all of the other staff will continue to take care of you. The business is staying within the family. So come on down, meet Matt when he's available, and continue to support local! ‚ô°‚ô°‚ô°

post_text: In response to our "news" today......yes, we had a burglary early this morning. Luckily, we were able to retrieve all the money and receipts that were taken. No information was compromised and everyone is okay! I have to say that the Central Point police department was on scene within two minutes of the call. A BIG thank you to them for their quick response and for their intuition!

CENTRAL POINT CAN YOU HELP! This is a terribly sad story and this family is in NO position to take care of his burial expenses...

Cody Shelton a young man that graduated from Crater in 2006 passed away in his sleep a few nights ago...his family is as to be expected just beside of themselves and struggling to come to grips with everything including the costs of everything! His name is Cody Shelton and an account is being set up at Chase Bank to help with all of the funeral & burial expenses...if you can donate anything at all please try to help this family that is as I said above struggling to just come to grips with his passing and then all of the cost of giving him the type of funeral and burial that he deserved...he was a GREAT young man...your help will be so greatly appreciated!!
